1. *Časni sudija* je donio odluku koja je bila u skladu sa zakonom. (Honorable judge made a decision that was in accordance with the law.)
2. Bilo je *časno* vidjeti kako su se susjedi brinuli o starim ljudima u zajednici. (It was honorable to see how neighbors took care of the elderly in the community.)
3. Želimo da *časno* predstavljamo našu zemlju na međunarodnom nivou. (We want to represent our country honorably on an international level.)
4. *Časna riječ* je najvažnija stvar u svakoj vezi. (Honorable word is the most important thing in every relationship.)
5. On je *časno* služio svoju zemlju tokom cijele svoje vojne karijere. (He honorably served his country throughout his military career.)
6. *Časni krst* je bio simbol pobjede u srednjem vijeku. (Honorable cross was a symbol of victory in the Middle Ages.)
7. Ovo je *časno* mjesto za život, ljudi su vrlo ljubazni i prijateljski raspoloženi. (This is an honorable place to live, people are very kind and friendly.)
8. *Časne sestre* su posvetile svoje živote služenju Bogu i pomaganju drugima. (Honorable sisters devoted their lives to serving God and helping others.)
9. *Časno zvanje* je ono koje se stječe velikim trudom i radom. (Honorable profession is the one that is acquired through great effort and hard work.)
10. Njegov *časni položaj* ga je doveo do pozicije gdje je mogao donositi važne odluke za društvo. (His honorable position brought him to a position where he could make important decisions for the society.)